# Research Digest Bot — example crontab entry
#
# Install:
#   crontab -e
#   (paste the line below, adjust the time if needed, save)
#
# Verify:
#   crontab -l           # confirm the entry is there
#   grep CRON /var/log/syslog   # check cron fired (after the scheduled time)
#
# Logs:
#   Pipeline logs go to data/logs/run-<id>.log inside the project.
#   Cron's own stderr (rare — e.g. uv not found) goes to the MAILTO address
#   or /var/mail/<user>. To redirect cron stderr to a file instead:
#     0 8 * * * /path/to/run-digest.sh 2>> /path/to/cron-errors.log
#
# Time format: minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week command
# The example below runs every day at 08:00 server local time.

0 8 * * * /home/greyson/projects/agentic/research-agent/scripts/run-digest.sh
